R9-E1 integration: a per-CLIP GLOBAL adaptive beta SELECTOR for the anchor blend.
DEFAULT-OFF -> byte-identical (anchor_blend_adaptive absent/None -> the fixed cfg
anchor_blend_beta path of R8-E3 is used unchanged; if that is also None the whole blend
is skipped). This is the R9-E1 hypothesis realized as a NARROW, opt-in research lever --
NOT a recommended default flip. R9-E1 VERDICT: fixed-0.85 (R8-E3) stays the robust default.

WHAT IT DOES (measured, R6-E1 degrade-restore matrix + a real-libx264 OOD, TRUE AlexNet
LPIPS arbiter + DISTS corroborator): beta = 0.85 - 0.15*s(tex_comp)*d(disag), a single
per-clip scalar in [0.70, 0.85], pulled DOWN toward 0.70 (more compact) ONLY on SMOOTH +
heavily-(synthetically)-degraded clips -- the ONLY cells with measured headroom below 0.85.
  tex_comp = mean 7x7 local-luma-STD of the COMPACT HR cache (degrade-ROBUST content: real
             texture survives heavy degrade where Canny edges collapse -- the falsifier that
             sank the LR-edge variant: texture46k|gritty edge=0.091 < talkinghead|moderate
             edge=0.087 yet wants opposite beta; tex_comp 17.97 vs 7.67 separates them 2x).
  disag    = mean |heavy - compact| luma (DEGRADE drive: x4plus over-sharpens synthetic
             noise/compression the compact net avoids -> high disagreement; a CLEAN real
             H.264 round-trip keeps both nets in agreement -> low disagreement).

MEASURED (zero-regression hand-set t=[9,14] d=[3.0,4.5], EXACT pixels): <= fixed-0.85 on all
23 cells (15 synthetic + 8 real-H.264 OOD); strictly beats 0.85 on the SMOOTH heavily-degraded
face (talkinghead heavy -0.0102, gritty -0.0134 LPIPS; DISTS-corroborated); TIES 0.85 on every
textured cell (0.85 is already the per-cell optimum there) and every mild/clean real-H.264 cell.

HONEST SCOPE (why DEFAULT OFF, see REPORT.md "threats"): (1) the win rides on ONE smooth-face
content (n=8) -- no independent smooth clip confirms it; (2) the d_lo degrade-gate floor (3.0)
must be set just ABOVE the measured real-H.264 disagreement level (~2.96) and is NOT learnable
from the synthetic operators alone -- a held-out synthetic calibration REGRESSES on real H.264
(+0.0006). The fixed-0.85 default is strictly more robust. (3) Anchor-only measurement; the
propagation/tOF effect is UNMEASURED (same caveat as R8-E3).

Cost: tex_comp + disag are two CPU reductions over the two caches the quality path ALREADY
holds (perframe_cache = x4plus, region_gate["compact"] = compact) -> ZERO extra SR.

SEAM (verify_patch.py): caller `derisk.select_anchor_beta(perframe_cache, region_gate["compact"],
cfg["anchor_blend_adaptive"])` -> handler `def select_anchor_beta(heavy_cache, compact_cache,
params)`; both caches dict[int]->HxWx3 uint8 at HD, identical keys; returns a float beta that is
fed straight into the EXISTING `blend_anchor_cache(...)` (R8-E3, unchanged). params=None -> the
fixed cfg beta is used (byte-identical to R8-E3); both None -> blend skipped (byte-identical to today).

